Preconditions:
The `locations` array must not be null.
The `locations` array must contain at least two elements.
The `start` and `finish` values must be valid indices within the `locations` array.
The `fuel` value must be a non-negative integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the count of all possible routes from `start` to `finish`.
The returned value should be modulo `10^9 + 7`.